                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16976.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My December 19, 6 p.m. Document just signed by Banda, Limon and Andalon
                    representing Governor Avila, other officers and about 4,000 troops. Former
                    General Yzabel Robles present and participating as sort of mediary. Turn-over
                    expected in Juarez to-day and in Chihuahua in few days. Villa left Chihuahua
                    with 800 men this morning; unknown destination.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
